### 1.3 Plan page: tasks and plan blanks must look visually different

**Problem:** In [PlanScreen.kt](file:///c:/Github/app/app/src/main/java/com/example/PlanScreen.kt), both `PlanTaskCard` and `SubTaskPlanCard` use the same `GlassCard` appearance.

#### [MODIFY] [PlanScreen.kt](file:///c:/Github/app/app/src/main/java/com/example/PlanScreen.kt)
- `PlanTaskCard` for time-boxed plans: add a colored left border or gradient accent (Indigo for local plans, Teal for calendar-synced, Coral for meetings)
- Floating/all-time tasks: keep current `GlassCard` but with a subtle different tint
- `SubTaskPlanCard`: use an indented card style with a connecting line to visually subordinate them

---

### 1.4 Plan page: no direct editing — single-click redirect and highlight

**Problem:** `PlanTaskCard` currently has an inline `Checkbox` for completion toggle AND edit/delete `IconButton`s. The prompt says users should not directly edit plans or subtasks on the plan page — only tasks for today/all time. 

#### [MODIFY] [PlanScreen.kt](file:///c:/Github/app/app/src/main/java/com/example/PlanScreen.kt)
- For **time-boxed plans**: remove the inline `Checkbox` and `Edit`/`Delete` buttons. Keep only the completion toggle (checkbox) for today's tasks.
- Clicking any plan card, subtask card, or today's task card once → redirect to the home page timeline and highlight it (pulsing glow border for 4 seconds) to show where it fits in the daily schedule.
- Edit/delete should only be reachable from double-click or the home screen timeline clicks.

---

### 1.5 Double-click on plan/subtask → open edit window

#### [MODIFY] [PlanScreen.kt](file:///c:/Github/app/app/src/main/java/com/example/PlanScreen.kt)
- Add `onDoubleClick` via `combinedClickable` to `GlassCard` wrapper.
- On plans/tasks: double-clicking opens `AddTaskDialog` in edit mode.
- On subtasks: double-clicking resolves the parent plan and opens the parent's edit dialog.

