## Phase 8 — Integrations

### 8.1 Alarm clock management ("Trainers")

Android provides `AlarmClock` intents to create system alarms programmatically. However, **reading/listing existing alarms is NOT possible** — there's no public API for that. What we CAN do:

- **Create alarms** from the app using `Intent.ACTION_SET_ALARM`
- **Schedule internal "alarm-like" reminders** using `AlarmManager` + full-screen notifications
- **Store alarm presets** in the app's own database ("Morning routine at 6:00", "Evening review at 21:00")

> [!WARNING]
> We cannot read or modify alarms set by other alarm clock apps. We can only create new ones via system intents.

#### [NEW] `AlarmPresetEntity.kt` — `com.example.data.local.entity`
- `id`, `userId`, `name`, `hour`, `minute`, `daysOfWeek` (bitmask), `isEnabled`, `linkedTaskTitle`

#### [NEW] `AlarmManager.kt` — `com.example.integrations`
- `createSystemAlarm(hour, minute, label)` — uses `Intent.ACTION_SET_ALARM`
- `scheduleInternalAlarm(preset)` — uses `AlarmManager.setAlarmClock()` for reliable wake-up

#### [MODIFY] [MainActivity.kt](file:///c:/Github/app/app/src/main/java/com/example/MainActivity.kt) — Home page
- Add "Alarms" option in the home page overflow/menu (compact, not taking much space)
- Shows list of alarm presets with toggle switches

#### [MODIFY] [AndroidManifest.xml](file:///c:/Github/app/app/src/main/AndroidManifest.xml)
- Add `SCHEDULE_EXACT_ALARM` permission for Android 12+
- Add `USE_EXACT_ALARM` permission for Android 14+

---

### 8.2 Xiaomi Smart Band 9 Pro

Xiaomi does **not** provide a public SDK for third-party apps. However, the Smart Band 9 Pro automatically **mirrors all Android notifications** via the **Mi Fitness** (formerly Zepp Life) companion app.

**What we need to do to ensure good band experience:**

#### [MODIFY] [NotificationHelper.kt](file:///c:/Github/app/app/src/main/java/com/example/notification/NotificationHelper.kt)
- Ensure notifications use `NotificationCompat.Builder` with:
  - Clear, short `contentTitle` (band displays ~20 chars)
  - Meaningful `contentText` (band shows first line)
  - Proper `category` hints (`CATEGORY_REMINDER`, `CATEGORY_EVENT`)
  - `setVisibility(VISIBILITY_PUBLIC)` so content shows on band
- The "Done" action button (Phase 6) will appear as a tappable action on the band

#### [MODIFY] [PlannerProApplication.kt](file:///c:/Github/app/app/src/main/java/com/example/PlannerProApplication.kt)
- Create notification channels with proper importance levels so Mi Fitness correctly categorizes them

> [!NOTE]
> No special SDK integration needed. As long as notifications are properly formatted and the user has Mi Fitness installed with notification access enabled, they will appear on the Smart Band 9 Pro automatically.

